name: Nut
title: Nut - Goddess of the Sky | Egyptian Mythology
subtitle: Goddess of the Sky and Heavens
shortDescription: Nut is the sky goddess whose body arches over the earth, swallowing the sun at dusk and giving birth to it at dawn. Mother of Osiris , Isis , Set , and Nephthys , born on the five epagomenal days won by Thoth . Her star-spangled body represents the night sky, and souls ascend to join her after death.
